channel.description: Learn Romanian in minutes with the Radio Lingua Network
channel.itunes:author: Radio Lingua Network
channel.itunes:summary: Join Romanian teacher Roxana and presenter Mark as they teach you the basics of Romanian. In this podcast you'll be learning just enough Romanian to get by on a holiday or business trip to Romania, or just to impress Romanian speakers everywhere! Each lesson includes just over one minute of language-learning content, so there's no excuse not to learn! Remember - even a few phrases of a language can help you make friends and enjoy travel more.

item.title: Promo - One Minute Romanian
item.description: Hello! My name is Roxana and I'd like to welcome you to One Minute Romanian from the Radio Lingua Network. In this podcast I'm going to be teaching you the basics of Romanian. The great thing about this language course is that you'll be learning all you need to know in just 60 seconds - or thereabouts! Each one minute language lesson will equip you with just enough Romanian to help you get by in lots of situations, either on holiday, or on a business trip to Romania, or just to impress your Romanian-speaking friends or colleagues. Our course will be starting very soon. In the meantime, visit our website on http://www.oneminutelanguages.com

item.title: Radio Lingua Network News: 26 September 2008
item.description: Happy European Day of Languages to all our listeners! By way of joining in this international celebration of languages and language-learning we're delighted to introduce eight new podcasts today. We're adding Catalan, Danish, French, Japanese, Mandarin and Romanian to our One Minute Languages series; we're introducing our first podcast for English learners - Write Back Soon will help learners master Phrasal Verbs; and we're finally announcing the long-awaited sequel to Coffee Break Spanish: it's Show Time!

item.title: One Minute Romanian - flyer
item.description: From the makers of the award-winning online language course Coffee Break Spanish comes a new range of titles aimed at busy people who want to acquire the absolute basics of a language. One Minute Languages from the Radio Lingua Network will introduce learners to a new language from scratch. The course is made up of ten lessons and covers topics including basic greetings, introducing yourself, and dealing with language problems. You’ll also learn numbers and other useful words and phrases which will help you communicate with native speakers in many situations. Being able to speak another language is not necessarily about being fluent: often just a few words and phrases can go a long way, and it’s amazing what you can achieve in just a few minutes! With One Minute Languages you’ll quickly learn the phrases you need to get to know people, to make travel easier or to communicate with your business colleagues. It’s all about making that good impression and showing that you’re willing to take that step. The clock is ticking, so let’s get learning! Start your free one-minute language lessons today by visiting our website on www.oneminutelanguages.com.
